---
// APEX 2016 detail page -- smallest/most budget-friendly stage in the fleet.
// Source: agl-reflections-website/stages/apex-2016.html (250 lines). Follows
// the shared detail-page pattern established by apex-5040.astro (Task 19,
// first dispatch): Layout/Header/PageHero/`.stage-cols` (prose + spec panel
// + figure + use-list + pairing, alongside StageSide) / QuoteCta / Footer.
//
// Like every stage hero (not just 5040's), this page's source has its own
// `.eng-bar` engineering-stat strip between the lede and the chip row
// (source line 95) -- rendered via PageHero's `afterLede` slot, same as the
// 5040 page. No "View Full Specs" / "View in 3D" CTAs here -- those are
// 5040-only. The source's "Download spec sheet" apex.miami PDF link (line
// 141) is dropped per the client's dead-link removal request; StageSide's
// `pdfRemoved` note covers that.
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/house/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/house/Footer.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import SpecTable from '../../components/SpecTable.astro';
import StageSide from '../../components/StageSide.astro';
import QuoteCta from '../../components/QuoteCta.astro';
import Kicker from '../../components/ui/Kicker.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';

import stage2016Hero from '../../assets/img/stage-2016-hero.webp';
import stage2016B from '../../assets/img/stage-2016-b.webp';

const specRows = [
  { label: 'Stage deck', value: '20′ × 16′' },
  { label: 'Stage height', value: '12′10″' },
  { label: 'Flybay capacity', value: '800 lb each' },
  { label: 'Total roof capacity', value: '3,400 lb' },
  { label: 'Access', value: 'Front-opening with aluminum stairs' },
  { label: 'Back wall', value: 'Removable modular panels — lower panels double as handrails' },
  { label: 'Options', value: 'Banner package available' },
  { label: 'Published rate', value: 'From $1,995 — as published; call to confirm your date' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="APEX 2016 Mobile Stage Rental | Reflections Productions"
  description="The APEX 2016 is a compact 20-by-16 mobile stage with 12 ft 10 in of stage height and a 3,400 lb roof capacity — budget-friendly, maneuverable and built to full APEX quality."
  path="/stages/apex-2016.html"
  ogImage="https://reflectionsproductions.com/assets/img/stage-2016-hero.webp"
>
  <Header currentPath="/stages/index.html" />

  <PageHero
    tall
    breadcrumb={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Stage Fleet', href: '/stages/index.html' }, { label: 'APEX 2016' }]}
    eyebrow="APEX"
    title="2016"
    lede="Small stage, no compromises: 20-by-16 deck, 12′10″ of height and a 3,400 lb roof capacity — <b>the perfect fit for smaller venues on real budgets.</b>"
    imageSrc={stage2016Hero}
    imageAlt="APEX 2016 stage dressed for the Formula E Fan Village with LED screen"
    chips={[
      { label: "20′ × 16′ DECK", variant: 'sandy' },
      { label: 'Hydraulic deployment' },
    ]}
  >
    <div class="eng-bar" slot="afterLede">
      <span class="eng-chip crowd">RIGHT FOR: UP TO 2,500 CROWDS</span>
      <span class="eng-chip">Front-opening design</span>
      <span class="eng-chip">800 lb per flybay · 3,400 lb roof</span>
      <span class="eng-chip">Aluminum stairs included</span>
      <span class="eng-chip">From $1,995</span>
    </div>
  </PageHero>

  <section class="band tight">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="stage-cols">
        <div>
          <div class="prose">
            <Kicker text="Overview" />
            <p>The APEX 2016 proves a compact stage doesn't have to feel like one. The fit and finish are excellent, the build is solid, and it flies 800 pounds on each flybay with a total roof capacity of 3,400 pounds — real production capability in a small footprint.</p>
            <p>The stage opens on the front side and comes with aluminum stairs and a removable modular back panel — the lower panels can stay in place as handrails or come out entirely. Easy to operate, maneuverable in tight areas and budget-friendly, it maintains APEX quality at community-event scale. An optional banner package is available.</p>
            <p>You've already seen this stage around town: most recently dressed as the <b>Formula E Fan Village stage at the 2025 Miami E-Prix</b>, wrapped in a custom branded arch with a full-width LED screen. <a class="arrow-link" href="/work/index.html">See it in Our Work</a></p>
          </div>

          <div id="specs" style="margin-top:44px">
            <SpecTable caption="APEX 2016 — Specifications" rows={specRows} />
            <p class="spec-note">Figures above are from the manufacturer spec sheet. Anything not listed: spec sheet on request — or call 786-504-2369 and we'll talk through your site.</p>
          </div>

          <figure class="figure" style="margin-top:44px">
            <Image src={stage2016B} alt="APEX 2016 stage in the yard with front opening and stairs deployed" loading="lazy" />
            <figcaption>2016 · front opening &amp; aluminum stairs</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <div style="margin-top:44px">
            <Kicker text="Built For" />
            <ul class="use-list">
              <li>Community events</li>
              <li>School functions</li>
              <li>Fan villages &amp; activations</li>
              <li>Small festivals</li>
              <li>Ceremonies &amp; rallies</li>
              <li>Tight urban sites</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="pairing" style="margin-top:40px">
            <h3>Make it a full production</h3>
            <p>Pair the 2016 with a <b>powered JBL system</b>, compact lighting and a backline package — a complete small-event production that still looks and sounds like a Reflections show.</p>
            <a class="arrow-link" href="/production/index.html">Production services</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <StageSide
          model="2016"
          pdfRemoved
          jumpLinks={[
            { label: 'Full specifications', href: '#specs' },
            { label: 'Compare the fleet', href: '/stages/index.html' },
          ]}
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <QuoteCta compact />

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .eng-bar {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px;
    margin: 26px 0 4px;
  }
  .eng-chip {
    border: 1px solid rgba(63, 167, 150, 0.45);
    color: var(--paper);
    font: 600 12px/1 var(--font-body);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 9px 13px;
    background: rgba(19, 94, 84, 0.14);
  }
  .eng-chip.crowd {
    border-color: rgba(255, 107, 74, 0.55);
    color: var(--gel-coral);
  }
</style>
